** About Cox Automotive **

Cox Automotive is the world’s largest automotive service organisation,
transforming the way the world buys, sells, owns and uses vehicles. As part of
the Cox family of businesses, we have been making our mark since 1898 by
building and evolving world-class businesses, helping over 40,000 clients
across five continents and bringing together the best solutions and teams.

** The role **

As a Technical BA, you will be working with a multi-disciplinary project team
through all aspects of the software development lifecycle starting from
design, through implementation and onto delivery, and ensuring that technical
constraints and considerations are documented and communicated in a timely
manner.

You will build strong relationships with key stakeholders, develop a deep
understanding of the product, facilitate workshops and interviews and make
your mark as a subject matter expert, ensuring a smooth delivery of product
strategy and the CAA’s strategic objectives.

** Responsibilities: **

  * Work closely with the Product Managers to translate high level product initiatives into detailed product requirements 
  * Facilitate workshops and interviews to elicit requirements and document current application functionality 
  * Prepare technical architecture and system configuration documents and diagrams 
  * Analyse proposed solutions for issues, risks and benefits, and their impact on CAA 
  * Simplify complex information to be easily understood by the business 
  * Work with the Product Manager, UX UI Designers, and Software Engineering teams to capture product and application requirements 
  * Complete modelling of application and business processes and identify opportunities for process improvements 
  * Become the subject matter expert for all assigned products applying technical business analysis frameworks to achieve the best outcomes 

** Skills & Experience: **

  * Tertiary qualification in an IT field including project management or business analysis would be advantageous 
  * Sound understanding of software development and software technology practices is essential 
  * Experience with the software development lifecycle and Agile methodology 
  * Exemplary communication and stakeholder management skills 
  * Highly creative with strong focus on analytical and pragmatic decision making 
  * Ability to document tasks for software systems using project management tools such as Jira and Confluence 

